  "description": [
    "I I THE PENSACOLA JOURNAL SATURDAY MORNING FEBRUARY 23 1907 5 PEOPLE AND EVENTS BY AURELIE MAREAN BERNARD I I No 669 Before 3 P M TelephosieNo 5 No 33 After 3 p M J Things of Interest To Women In olden days the wives of chief tains often urged their lords to the slaughter and the chase today the highest women to the land head move ments for the suppression of cruelty to man and beast and bird humanity i and kindness to all living creaturesj To discourage the cruelty practised on birds has been the especial effort I of certain humane women As has been pointed out the chief cruelty practised In obtaining the most cov eted plumage Is that It is generally taken from the birds when nesting and In consequence of killing the parent birds the little ones are left to die of starvation Naturally this wanton destruction of bird life would result in its own punishment for the species would ultimately become ex tinct This also applies very largely of course to such birds as the humming bird and the bird of paradise which are extensively hunted for the sake of their beautiful plumage These"
